8. Relationship to Applications

(Unchanged, but now enforced)

Applications:

Provide raw inputs

Supply orientation defaults

Implement domain-specific interpretation/scoring

Persist and display outputs

Applications do not:

Define information types

Bypass invariants

Collapse uncertainty

Execute action without orientation and validation

9. Sequential Update Strategy (Maintaining Awareness)

(Unchanged)

This document is living and versioned.

Each update must:

State why the change exists

Specify which layer changed

Note downstream implications

Allowed:

New invariants

Metadata refinement

New kernel models

Disallowed (without explicit review):

Collapsing model boundaries

Allowing action without orientation

Opaque or un-auditable scoring

10. Definition of “Done” (for the Kernel)

(Clarified)

The kernel is functionally complete when:

Every Recommendation is fully traceable to Observations and Evidence

Uncertainty mechanically constrains action

Proportionate Action is enforced by invariants

Review produces explicit, auditable updates

No domain logic exists in core layers

At that point, applications and policies can safely build on top.

11. Canonical Summary

The Thinking Constitution Engine is a cognitive governance kernel that makes decision-making:

Explicit

Auditable

Value-aware

Uncertainty-sensitive

— while preserving human agency.

